						               													<description>Fato Fake is a knowledge contest. Do you think you know enough? So prepare your memory and let's get started.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Start of the game: Each player chooses a color among the available pins and the oldest player shuffles the cards and places them stacked in the indicated place on the board, with the back side facing up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With all the pins in the &amp;ldquo;start&amp;rdquo; box. &amp;#10;The first must advance one space on the board, remove the first card from the pile and, without looking, hand it over to the player on your right. Then, you must turn the roulette wheel. If the pointer stops at of the colored boxes, the player with the card reads the question with the corresponding color on the card and, at the end of the statement read, asks: &amp;ldquo;Fact or fake? &amp;rdquo;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the player gets it right, he gets the card. If he misses, the card goes to a lot of discard.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Attention: If the pointer stops over the &amp;ldquo;CHALLENGE&amp;rdquo; box, the player must point any player, according to his strategy, to respond.&amp;#10;If the chosen player gets it right, he keeps the card; if he misses, the player who challenged him stays with her.&amp;#10;But wait! Do you think it's easy? If the roulette stops on the &amp;ldquo;AZAR&amp;rdquo; box, the player must answer 2 questions to keep the card. For example: If he hits the first and misses the second, he will be forced to hit the third to keep the card. If you miss 2 questions, the letter goes to lot of disposal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The next one on the left removes a card from the pile on the board, advances one square and repeats the process.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when the first player reaches the final square. At that point, all players count their cards. Win that one that got it right and, consequently, has more cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
